WEBVTT

00:07.616 --> 00:09.376
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

00:37.833 --> 00:41.213
[All characters and events are fictional,
and any resemblance is coincidental]

00:41.213 --> 00:43.833
[Scenes with children and animals were filmed
safely under professional supervision]

00:45.667 --> 00:48.000
Shall we wrap up the class here today?

00:48.000 --> 00:50.667
- Thank you.
- Thank you, professor.

01:05.667 --> 01:07.392
Officer Lee.

01:10.000 --> 01:12.133
Aren't you a little too old

01:13.133 --> 01:15.167
to take my class?

01:15.167 --> 01:17.367
'Officer Lee.'

01:17.367 --> 01:19.467
Hearing you call me that

01:19.467 --> 01:23.100
makes me feel young again, Detective Kang.

01:23.100 --> 01:27.700
Sorry, shouldn't have called you that.
You've been Chief Inspector for a while.

01:27.700 --> 01:30.400
The Kangseng Serial Murder Case.

01:31.967 --> 01:34.167
The real culprit has been caught.

01:36.433 --> 01:38.600
It's been 30 years.

01:40.640 --> 01:42.800
[Prisoner Info Card
Lee Yong Woo]

01:42.800 --> 01:46.200
He lived in Kangseng County at the time,

01:46.200 --> 01:49.267
and later moved to Cheongju.

01:49.267 --> 01:53.767
He was sentenced to life in 1994
for killing his sister-in-law

01:53.767 --> 01:56.300
and has been serving his sentence ever since.

01:57.667 --> 01:59.833
He was in prison?

02:00.833 --> 02:02.167
That's why...

02:02.167 --> 02:04.400
We happened to visit

02:04.400 --> 02:08.467
right after Lee Yong Woo's
parole hearing had ended.

02:08.467 --> 02:14.000
If we'd been any later, he would've been
released as a model prisoner.

02:15.667 --> 02:18.100
Just thinking about it gives me chills.

02:18.100 --> 02:21.333
The problem is, Lee Yong Woo's DNA was found

02:21.333 --> 02:23.767
in only three cases.

02:23.767 --> 02:25.216
Therefore,

02:25.216 --> 02:27.667
we'll need his confession for the rest cases.

02:28.967 --> 02:31.800
Even though the statute
of limitations passed,

02:31.800 --> 02:35.000
getting his confession won't be easy.

02:37.467 --> 02:39.200
Sir.

02:39.867 --> 02:41.900
Please help us.

02:41.900 --> 02:45.633
You wanted to catch the culprit
more than anyone.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.954
[Lee Yong Woo]

03:04.433 --> 03:06.240
Actually,

03:06.240 --> 03:09.400
Lee Yong Woo requested it himself.

03:09.400 --> 03:11.833
He asked for you specifically.

03:16.700 --> 03:18.400
Me?

03:44.704 --> 03:48.200
[Female body discovered in Kangseng County]

03:48.200 --> 03:51.322
[Public frustration grows
as investigation stalls]

04:08.400 --> 04:10.333
We'll now present the commendations.

04:10.333 --> 04:12.200
[1988 Awards Ceremony
for Outstanding Police Officers]

04:12.200 --> 04:14.810
[Episode 1]

04:42.667 --> 04:44.367
These seats are reserved for the awardees.

04:44.367 --> 04:46.133
Spectators sit in the back.

04:46.133 --> 04:48.467
It's empty anyway, so what's the big deal?

04:49.900 --> 04:54.600
Next, we will present commendations
to Jongno Police officers

04:54.600 --> 04:56.867
for their assistance
in apprehending an organized crime group.

04:56.867 --> 04:58.133
Please step forward upon hearing your name.

04:58.133 --> 05:00.233
Can't you hear me?

05:00.233 --> 05:03.000
That's not your seat.

05:03.000 --> 05:05.540
Aren't we both just sitting

05:05.540 --> 05:07.533
where we shouldn't be?

05:08.233 --> 05:10.900
Then you shouldn't have let it be taken.

05:10.900 --> 05:13.333
The one who can't keep it is the fool.

05:13.333 --> 05:15.833
Right? Now that's more like it.

05:15.833 --> 05:18.633
Otherwise, there'd be
no point in coming here.

05:19.500 --> 05:21.900
I came to flip this whole thing over.

05:21.900 --> 05:23.433
And I might as well make it loud.

05:23.433 --> 05:25.833
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

05:25.833 --> 05:29.767
Quit the act and get lost.
I'll buy you drinks someday.

05:33.867 --> 05:35.733
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

05:36.833 --> 05:39.400
I'm arresting you on charges of bribery.

05:39.400 --> 05:41.367
Are you out of your mind?
Get these off me now.

05:41.367 --> 05:44.400
You know Kim Dae Pyeong,
Dosan gang's second-in-command, don't you?

05:44.400 --> 05:46.233
The one who gave you the money.

05:46.233 --> 05:47.600
I... I don't know anything about it.

05:47.600 --> 05:48.867
Just take these off first.

05:48.867 --> 05:50.300
Sergeant Choi Jung Mo.

05:50.300 --> 05:51.367
- Hey!
- Is Sergeant Choi Jung Mo here?

05:51.367 --> 05:54.433
Don't you see you're making things
difficult for Chief too?

05:54.433 --> 05:56.200
You really want to stand there that much?

05:56.200 --> 05:59.000
Hurry up and take these off me.

06:00.233 --> 06:02.233
Fine, fine.

06:02.233 --> 06:05.633
There it is, here.

06:13.633 --> 06:17.133
The officer he just awarded
turns out to be corrupt.

06:17.133 --> 06:18.567
Think carefully.

06:18.567 --> 06:21.933
Which will embarrass Chief more?

06:28.416 --> 06:30.767
- Darn it.
- Good call.

06:33.500 --> 06:37.433
That's enough of a scene.
Let's head out peacefully.

06:37.433 --> 06:40.300
Come on, keep your head up.

06:44.333 --> 06:49.133
Let's continue with the awards.

07:00.467 --> 07:03.967
Earlier during the ceremony,
a police officer was unexpectedly arrested.

07:03.967 --> 07:07.167
Is it true there was a corrupt officer
among the award recipients?

07:07.167 --> 07:08.533
Did you know and still turn a blind eye?

07:08.533 --> 07:10.533
Please answer us.

07:10.533 --> 07:12.600
Was this meant as a warning?

07:12.600 --> 07:13.833
You've always said

07:13.833 --> 07:17.800
no amount of achievement
can excuse corruption in public office.

07:17.800 --> 07:21.600
So did you just
demonstrate that belief in action?

07:24.833 --> 07:25.933
That is correct.

07:25.933 --> 07:28.900
Then, was that earlier incident
ordered by you, Chief?

07:28.900 --> 07:31.867
I believed that rather than covering up
wrongdoing within our own ranks,

07:31.867 --> 07:34.267
exposing it and asking for forgiveness

07:34.267 --> 07:38.700
is what makes a police force
worthy of public trust.

07:38.700 --> 07:40.200
I sincerely apologize

07:40.200 --> 07:43.167
to the public for the police's involvement

07:43.167 --> 07:46.016
in this unfortunate incident.

07:46.016 --> 07:47.633
[Auditorium]

07:47.633 --> 07:51.700
[No Mercy for Corruption,
A Bold Move by the Police Chief]

08:03.600 --> 08:05.300
I've come back

08:06.967 --> 08:08.100
home.

08:08.100 --> 08:10.367
Darn it.

08:13.933 --> 08:17.933
[Kangseng]

08:20.067 --> 08:24.967
[If you don't turn yourself in,
your limbs will rot and you'll die]

08:31.067 --> 08:32.100
Is that him?

08:32.100 --> 08:33.267
The most handsome guy in Kangseng?

08:33.267 --> 08:35.133
Yeah, they say he looks like Andy Lau.

08:35.133 --> 08:36.300
No way!

08:36.300 --> 08:37.633
There's an Andy Lau in Kangseng?

08:37.633 --> 08:40.033
I'm telling you!

08:41.533 --> 08:43.633
- Oh, come on!
- Just a middle-aged guy.

08:43.633 --> 08:45.367
What a waste of time.

08:45.367 --> 08:46.367
More like Sammo Hung.

08:46.367 --> 08:48.200
Hey, come on. What is this really?

08:48.200 --> 08:49.600
- Seriously?
- What's going on?

08:49.600 --> 08:51.500
Come on, Andy Lau? Give me a break.

08:51.500 --> 08:54.133
Who started that rumor that he's handsome?

08:57.933 --> 09:00.133
Yes, this is Kangseng Bookstore.

09:00.133 --> 09:03.400
Hey, with a face like that,
I'd pack him lunch every day.

09:03.400 --> 09:04.433
He just made eye contact with me.

09:04.433 --> 09:06.967
Ki Hwan.

09:06.967 --> 09:08.900
- Call for you.
- Okay.

09:08.900 --> 09:10.560
He's so hot!

09:10.560 --> 09:13.200
His eyes are like a deer's.

09:13.200 --> 09:14.900
Hello?

09:16.433 --> 09:19.233
Oh, Ji Won.

09:19.233 --> 09:21.800
What? Tae Joo is back?

09:21.800 --> 09:24.467
Okay, I'll be right there.

09:24.467 --> 09:26.867
[Handcuffed Corrupt Cop at Awards Ceremony]
While others ran Chief with his head down,

09:26.867 --> 09:28.467
[Auntie's Restaurant]
we ran you instead.

09:28.467 --> 09:30.400
Kangseng's own madman, Kang Tae Joo.

09:30.400 --> 09:34.267
Wow, with that cigarette,
you look just like Chow Yun Fat.

09:34.267 --> 09:35.700
It's not... not a cigarette.

09:35.700 --> 09:37.867
Stop right there! You punk!

09:40.467 --> 09:41.667
Hey!

09:41.667 --> 09:43.333
Where do you think you're running off to?

09:43.333 --> 09:45.033
You punk!

09:45.033 --> 09:46.533
[Auntie's Restaurant]
Stop, you!

09:46.533 --> 09:49.133
Aren't those Detective Do and Detective Jang?

09:51.100 --> 09:54.100
- You're not going after him?
- My assignment starts tomorrow.

09:54.100 --> 09:55.400
So you're just letting him go?

09:55.400 --> 09:57.833
He's clearly just a small-time crook.

09:58.496 --> 10:00.567
I've told you, don't hit my head!

10:00.567 --> 10:02.500
Kang Tae Joo!

10:02.500 --> 10:05.767
You are so full of yourself now
after living in Seoul.

10:05.767 --> 10:08.167
Detective, please help me.

10:08.167 --> 10:10.600
- I really didn't do it.
- Who is he?

10:10.600 --> 10:11.900
A guy I put behind bars before.

10:11.900 --> 10:13.733
- Hey, what is it?
- When I got caught by you,

10:13.733 --> 10:15.300
I didn't feel it was unfair!

10:15.300 --> 10:16.367
Why? What? Go away!

10:16.367 --> 10:18.880
You punk!

10:20.200 --> 10:21.233
Detective.

10:21.233 --> 10:23.300
Good grief.

10:23.967 --> 10:25.767
Detective Kang?

10:25.767 --> 10:28.800
How long has it been? Three years?

10:28.800 --> 10:30.533
Oh my.

10:30.533 --> 10:33.267
I heard you got kicked out of Seoul.

10:33.267 --> 10:38.067
You left like you'd never return.
Look at you now.

10:41.133 --> 10:42.567
I'm innocent!

10:42.567 --> 10:44.067
I really didn't do anything!

10:44.067 --> 10:46.733
Alright, let's go.

10:46.733 --> 10:48.967
Detective.

10:48.967 --> 10:50.700
We'll talk tomorrow.

10:50.700 --> 10:53.733
I'm telling you, I didn't do anything!

10:53.733 --> 10:57.267
- You!
- It's not me!

11:01.000 --> 11:02.368
You...

11:02.368 --> 11:04.300
You got kicked out?

11:05.000 --> 11:06.733
Why?

11:07.567 --> 11:10.067
[Handcuffed Corrupt Cop at Awards Ceremony]
Move it. Look, is this what it's about?

11:10.067 --> 11:11.433
Smoking in front of the Chief?

11:11.433 --> 11:13.400
I told you, it wasn't a cigarette!

11:13.400 --> 11:15.400
Then what was it?

11:21.467 --> 11:24.567
I locked up a guy
who took bribes from gangsters.

11:24.567 --> 11:27.500
Turns out he's
the Police Commissioner's nephew.

11:27.500 --> 11:29.567
So I got transferred out of nowhere.

11:29.567 --> 11:32.833
This is ridiculous. Isn't that retaliation?

11:34.467 --> 11:38.067
Hey, Tae Joo, are you really okay?

11:38.067 --> 11:39.600
Why wouldn't I be?

11:39.600 --> 11:41.367
Seriously, it was huge.

11:41.367 --> 11:42.700
We sold so much today.

11:42.700 --> 11:45.267
Oh? Tae Joo.

11:45.267 --> 11:48.567
Hey, it's been a while, guys.

11:48.567 --> 11:50.800
You're a newlywed,
so you should head home early.

11:50.800 --> 11:53.600
I'm out for the first time in a while.

11:53.600 --> 11:55.633
Tae Joo, it's really been ages.

11:55.633 --> 11:58.267
Right, Un Hui,
I heard you're working under Ji Won.

11:58.267 --> 11:59.633
- Yes.
- Hey.

11:59.633 --> 12:02.833
We're not in the mood for greetings now,
so if you're here to eat, then eat.

12:02.833 --> 12:05.467
If you can get inside in three seconds,
I'm paying for your meals.

12:06.234 --> 12:09.466
Come on, move!

12:09.466 --> 12:10.624
Sit down!

12:13.633 --> 12:15.667
What's going on with them?

12:15.667 --> 12:17.700
Something wrong?

12:17.700 --> 12:20.767
When Ms. Seo is acting like that,
it's pretty serious.

12:20.767 --> 12:23.667
Hey, isn't it weird
calling your own sister "Ms. Seo"?

12:23.667 --> 12:28.300
I called her "Ji Won" at the newsroom
and got hit for it.

12:28.300 --> 12:29.733
She still hits people?

12:29.733 --> 12:32.033
Ah, don't even ask.

12:32.033 --> 12:34.967
Ki Beom, did you get caught or something?

12:36.667 --> 12:40.933
Come on, if so, he'd be sitting over there.

12:40.933 --> 12:42.000
Whatever.

12:42.000 --> 12:43.433
What's he gonna do, kill me?

12:43.433 --> 12:45.167
Cheers.

12:46.300 --> 12:48.500
Hey, forget it.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.433
Let's just go all the way tonight.

12:50.433 --> 12:52.300
Just don't pass out before sunrise, alright?

12:52.300 --> 12:54.033
Okay.

12:56.096 --> 12:57.984
It's not that way.

12:59.567 --> 13:01.533
Hold on, we're almost there.

13:01.533 --> 13:02.633
It's Sun Young.

13:02.633 --> 13:04.700
Hey, pull yourself together.

13:04.700 --> 13:06.833
- Sun Young!
- Pull yourself together.

13:06.833 --> 13:08.033
Hey, Sun Young...

13:08.033 --> 13:09.700
Hey, act sober. Pretend you're fine.

13:09.700 --> 13:10.733
Sun Young.

13:10.733 --> 13:13.200
Hold on, you're too heavy.

13:13.200 --> 13:16.133
Should we lay him down here?

13:16.133 --> 13:17.133
Oh, my back.

13:17.133 --> 13:18.733
Sun Young.

13:18.733 --> 13:20.467
Sun Young.

13:26.233 --> 13:27.267
Jeez.

13:27.267 --> 13:30.267
Oh, I'm home.

13:31.000 --> 13:33.233
The smell...

13:35.000 --> 13:38.367
It's you, our Sun Young.

13:38.367 --> 13:39.500
Sun Young is mad.

13:39.500 --> 13:40.500
How much did you drink?

13:40.500 --> 13:42.267
My pretty little sister, my...

13:42.267 --> 13:44.000
Jeez, you idiot,

13:44.000 --> 13:45.900
lay off the booze a little.

13:45.900 --> 13:47.667
I'm...

13:47.667 --> 13:49.867
Seriously, what is this?

13:53.700 --> 13:55.033
Is he dead?

13:55.033 --> 13:56.867
Well...

14:00.267 --> 14:03.267
We didn't see anything, Sun Young.

14:03.267 --> 14:04.300
We're leaving.

14:04.300 --> 14:05.700
Ki Hwan, let's go.

14:05.700 --> 14:07.467
Is he dead?

14:07.467 --> 14:08.960
Good night.

14:08.960 --> 14:11.459
- Is he dead?
- Shut up!

14:39.000 --> 14:43.700
Dead or alive?

14:43.700 --> 14:47.600
Dead or alive?

14:49.100 --> 14:51.200
Alive!

15:27.067 --> 15:33.867
[Period for Reporting and Surrendering Spies]

15:33.867 --> 15:37.000
[Stop]

15:56.733 --> 16:00.333
Excuse me, who are you
to sit in someone else's seat?

16:04.700 --> 16:05.833
It was my seat before.

16:05.833 --> 16:07.933
Hey, what do you mean 'your seat'?

16:07.933 --> 16:09.300
This is where the youngest sits now.

16:09.300 --> 16:11.300
It's not like you were born in that chair.

16:11.300 --> 16:13.504
Just sit over there. It's empty anyway.

16:13.504 --> 16:14.533
Ugh, it's...

16:14.533 --> 16:16.500
It still reeks of your cigarettes.

16:16.500 --> 16:19.067
It stinks there.

16:19.067 --> 16:21.767
You've become a real Seoul snob.
You're the only one who smells it?

16:21.767 --> 16:25.500
This used to be my seat.

16:29.367 --> 16:30.400
Rookie?

16:30.400 --> 16:32.200
Yes, I'm Park Dae Ho.

16:32.200 --> 16:33.500
Okay, rookie.

16:33.500 --> 16:38.533
I've been in Seoul the whole time.

16:38.533 --> 16:40.333
Have you been to Seoul?

16:40.333 --> 16:41.367
- No.
- Oh my.

16:41.367 --> 16:44.000
Then you have no idea
how bad the air is there.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.333
Factories, car exhaust...

16:46.333 --> 16:50.033
I was about to get lung disease,
so I begged to come here.

16:50.033 --> 16:51.133
Just to survive.

16:51.133 --> 16:53.000
Really?

16:54.033 --> 16:55.100
Please stay seated there.

16:55.100 --> 16:56.833
Hey, you believe him?

16:56.833 --> 17:01.067
Look at his complexion.
He looks perfectly fine, oh my.

17:01.067 --> 17:05.400
If you feel wronged,
just take it as saving a life. Okay?

17:05.400 --> 17:07.167
Lee Seong Jin!

17:10.867 --> 17:12.700
Lee Seong Jin, you...

17:14.833 --> 17:16.733
Hey, Lee Seong Jin!

17:18.233 --> 17:19.933
[Security Interview Room]
You...

17:26.600 --> 17:28.533
What kind of world is this nowadays?

17:28.533 --> 17:31.267
Just to get a confession,
you beat him up like that?

17:31.267 --> 17:32.333
If this were in Seoul,

17:32.333 --> 17:34.000
it'd be front-page news.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.333
Hey! You think working in Seoul
makes you special?

17:36.333 --> 17:37.833
So what, you punk?

17:37.833 --> 17:40.900
The prosecutor is demanding
we get a confession today, no matter what.

17:40.900 --> 17:44.700
I've arrested that guy
three times, so I know him.

17:44.700 --> 17:49.400
If you hit him with solid evidence,
he just stammers and spills everything.

17:49.400 --> 17:53.233
It's not like he killed anyone.
Why treat some petty crook like that?

17:58.167 --> 18:00.367
Why? What is it?

18:01.267 --> 18:03.000
Hey.

18:04.833 --> 18:07.500
He did kill someone.

18:07.500 --> 18:09.767
He's a murderer.

18:09.767 --> 18:11.467
What?

18:26.467 --> 18:31.633
With the Olympics just a month away,
things are very unsettled.

18:31.633 --> 18:34.133
Given the situation,
everyone stay careful, understood?

18:34.133 --> 18:36.167
- Yes.
- Everyone here?

18:36.167 --> 18:37.900
Yes.

18:39.167 --> 18:41.900
I heard the suspect in the Im Bok Hee
murder case has been caught.

18:43.300 --> 18:45.033
As expected of Prosecutor Cha.

18:45.033 --> 18:47.400
You really know how to get things done.

18:47.400 --> 18:48.900
I'm flattered.

18:48.900 --> 18:53.033
If we hadn't solved this case,
I would've lost my job.

18:53.033 --> 18:55.267
You know we already have
two unsolved cases at the station, right?

18:55.267 --> 18:57.900
And both are murder cases.

18:57.900 --> 18:59.733
Sorry, I feel ashamed.

19:00.533 --> 19:03.033
This is why the first step matters.

19:03.033 --> 19:06.233
If you're not confident,
why not hand it over to Mr. Cha now?

19:06.233 --> 19:07.400
No need, sir.

19:07.400 --> 19:10.700
It's my case, so I'll see it through.

19:17.533 --> 19:20.367
- Send it to me by tomorrow.
- Yes, sir.

19:23.933 --> 19:25.633
Mr. Cha!

19:25.633 --> 19:27.933
- Oh, yes.
- About the suspect.

19:27.933 --> 19:29.568
How did you find him?

19:30.700 --> 19:33.700
The method of strangling the victim
with stockings was unusual.

19:33.700 --> 19:37.067
So I started with offenders
with stocking-related records.

19:37.067 --> 19:39.567
Turns out one of them lived nearby.

19:39.567 --> 19:43.667
We also got a witness
who saw him near the scene.

19:43.667 --> 19:45.933
Isn't that only natural?

19:45.933 --> 19:49.233
He lives near the crime scene, you said.

19:49.233 --> 19:53.300
So there's still no direct evidence, right?

19:53.300 --> 19:54.833
Make sure you check thoroughly.

19:54.833 --> 19:56.967
Don't end up like me.

20:05.133 --> 20:07.584
He's tougher than I expected.

20:07.584 --> 20:09.100
So please allow me a little more time.

20:09.100 --> 20:11.167
I'll get a confession out of him.

20:11.167 --> 20:13.867
No direct evidence?

20:15.033 --> 20:16.067
He's quite the expert.

20:16.067 --> 20:17.167
Excuse me?

20:17.167 --> 20:20.400
What do you mean by that?

20:20.400 --> 20:22.767
Are you sure Lee Seong Jin is the culprit?

20:22.767 --> 20:24.767
Of course.

20:24.767 --> 20:27.033
I mean, there's a witness too.

20:27.033 --> 20:30.400
But that witness didn't
actually see the crime happen.

20:30.400 --> 20:32.600
He said he just saw him nearby.

20:32.600 --> 20:34.233
He's local, not from Seoul.

20:34.233 --> 20:35.800
Does that really count as evidence?

20:35.800 --> 20:40.967
Well, the blood type at the scene is B,

20:40.967 --> 20:43.700
and Lee Seong Jin is also type B...

20:45.067 --> 20:47.300
I'm type B too!

20:49.867 --> 20:51.533
You're really doing it like amateurs!

20:51.533 --> 20:53.233
Sorry.

20:59.500 --> 21:01.024
Lee Seong Jin...

21:01.792 --> 21:03.667
I need to meet him myself.

21:04.667 --> 21:08.600
In February last year,
he was fined for stealing stockings.

21:08.600 --> 21:10.933
[Criminal Record Certificate]

21:14.833 --> 21:17.900
Served from April to July. What was it for?

21:17.900 --> 21:20.700
Well, indecent assault.

21:20.700 --> 21:23.233
He touched a woman's leg
as she was passing by in stockings.

21:23.233 --> 21:26.100
I told that guy to live a decent life...

21:27.200 --> 21:30.800
Anyway, so it's just theft
and indecent assault, right?

21:30.800 --> 21:34.033
Yes, this would be his first murder.

21:34.833 --> 21:37.067
Who says he killed anyone?

21:37.067 --> 21:40.067
Don't jump to conclusions.
Nothing's been proven yet.

21:40.067 --> 21:41.800
Yes, sir.

21:42.500 --> 21:43.933
Bring me the case files
and crime scene photos

21:43.933 --> 21:46.067
of that Im Bok Hee murder case.

21:46.067 --> 21:48.333
Okay, one moment.

21:56.608 --> 21:57.667
- Jeez.
- I'm...

21:57.667 --> 21:59.367
I'm sorry.

22:01.233 --> 22:05.733
Hey, if you just grab everything like that,
how are you going to sort it out later?

22:05.733 --> 22:07.267
Jeez.

22:07.267 --> 22:08.967
Sorry.

22:21.300 --> 22:22.567
Stop right there.

22:22.567 --> 22:23.904
Huh?

22:23.904 --> 22:26.167
Why? What's wrong?

22:39.500 --> 22:41.433
What is this?

22:41.433 --> 22:43.488
This is...

22:43.488 --> 22:44.736
Why are the bodies all different?

22:44.736 --> 22:47.767
These are the murder cases
that have occurred recently.

22:47.767 --> 22:49.433
Three in total.

22:49.433 --> 22:51.433
Three?

22:51.433 --> 22:52.467
And the killer?

22:52.467 --> 22:54.167
It's still...

22:56.833 --> 22:58.767
What's wrong?

23:01.367 --> 23:03.067
These are

23:04.233 --> 23:06.200
serial murders.

23:10.833 --> 23:12.533
Lee Seong Jin!

23:13.467 --> 23:15.733
Lee Seong... Hey, where's Lee Seong Jin?

23:15.733 --> 23:17.900
Detective Jang and Detective Do...

23:17.900 --> 23:20.833
- There they are.
- Come over.

23:20.833 --> 23:22.200
Lee Seong Jin!

23:22.200 --> 23:24.400
Lee Seong Jin, it wasn't you, right?

23:24.400 --> 23:25.533
What are you talking about?

23:25.533 --> 23:27.067
He's not the real killer!

23:27.067 --> 23:29.300
Hey, you said it yourself
it wasn't you, right?

23:29.300 --> 23:31.433
No. It was me!

23:31.433 --> 23:33.367
I did it!

23:34.533 --> 23:36.033
What's wrong with you?

23:36.033 --> 23:37.500
Seong Jin.

23:37.500 --> 23:38.500
Stop it, you punk.

23:38.500 --> 23:39.633
He already confessed everything.

23:39.633 --> 23:41.867
- Ji Hwan, lock him up.
- Yes, sir.

23:48.700 --> 23:50.167
You beat him again, didn't you?

23:50.167 --> 23:51.667
Is that even a real confession?

23:51.667 --> 23:53.133
It's not like that, you punk.

23:53.133 --> 23:54.900
Don't talk back to me like that.

23:54.900 --> 23:56.633
Don't give me that.

23:57.400 --> 23:58.767
Tell me straight.

23:58.767 --> 24:01.000
The prosecutor in charge got it himself.

24:01.000 --> 24:02.700
The confession.

24:05.700 --> 24:06.752
[Name: Lee Seong Jin, currently unemployed]

24:06.752 --> 24:07.840
[I lost my father in childhood
and live with my mother]

24:21.467 --> 24:24.133
- Mr. Lee Seong Jin.
- Yes.

24:24.133 --> 24:26.467
Why are you shaking?

24:26.467 --> 24:28.992
You're a prosecutor, aren't you?

24:29.733 --> 24:32.267
Prosecutors aren't scary people.

24:32.267 --> 24:34.714
We're only scary to people
who've committed crimes.

24:35.400 --> 24:38.200
Mr. Lee, have you done anything wrong?

24:42.033 --> 24:43.616
So you

24:43.616 --> 24:45.800
really didn't kill Im Bok Hee?

24:45.800 --> 24:46.810
I didn't.

24:47.867 --> 24:50.967
Oh dear, then you were just unlucky.

24:50.967 --> 24:53.600
You happened to live in that neighborhood.

25:02.933 --> 25:05.033
Then,

25:05.033 --> 25:06.880
Mr. Lee,

25:06.880 --> 25:09.133
can you help me out a bit?

25:10.733 --> 25:13.133
I really can't figure it out.

25:13.133 --> 25:18.400
Why did the killer use
stockings to kill someone?

25:19.900 --> 25:23.333
You have a certain expertise with stockings.

25:23.333 --> 25:26.067
That's why you ended up under suspicion too.

25:28.533 --> 25:30.304
Mr. Lee,

25:30.304 --> 25:31.800
why do you like stockings?

25:32.698 --> 25:34.967
Well...

25:34.967 --> 25:38.267
This is...

25:40.767 --> 25:43.967
At first, they feel soft.

25:43.967 --> 25:46.200
But if you keep touching them,

25:46.200 --> 25:49.400
they all become rough.

25:49.400 --> 25:53.933
That feeling is strangely intense.

25:53.933 --> 25:55.633
So it was you.

25:56.267 --> 25:57.967
What?

26:02.200 --> 26:05.800
I wasn't sure until I came here.

26:12.367 --> 26:14.667
But your eyes gave it away.

26:14.667 --> 26:17.400
Those totally fried eyes.

26:18.500 --> 26:19.633
You killed her, didn't you?

26:19.633 --> 26:20.767
No, I didn't.

26:20.767 --> 26:22.967
I didn't kill her.

26:22.967 --> 26:25.367
Listen carefully.

26:25.367 --> 26:28.733
This is the first and last chance
I'm giving you.

26:30.667 --> 26:32.096
Today,

26:32.096 --> 26:34.667
if you confess here,

26:34.667 --> 26:37.533
I'll get you out within five years.

26:37.533 --> 26:38.816
However,

26:38.816 --> 26:42.767
if you don't confess
before I walk out that door?

26:42.767 --> 26:45.667
You'll rot in prison forever.

26:45.667 --> 26:47.467
Got it?

26:48.433 --> 26:50.633
- What?
- One,

26:51.300 --> 26:53.167
two,

26:53.167 --> 26:55.000
three,

26:55.000 --> 26:57.467
- four.
- No, please, Mr. Cha.

26:57.467 --> 26:58.967
Sir!

26:58.967 --> 27:01.000
Please save me.

27:01.000 --> 27:03.800
I'm all my mother has.

27:03.800 --> 27:05.400
She's sick right now.

27:05.400 --> 27:06.933
Oh dear.

27:06.933 --> 27:10.467
Then if you don't confess,
you won't even get out by her 80th birthday.

27:10.467 --> 27:11.967
No, please don't.

27:11.967 --> 27:14.400
- Five,
- Sir!

27:14.400 --> 27:16.333
- six,
- No, sir.

27:16.333 --> 27:18.867
- seven...
- Please spare me.

27:18.867 --> 27:21.833
I'll let you attend your mother's funeral
as the chief mourner.

27:21.833 --> 27:23.200
So don't worry.

27:23.200 --> 27:25.567
No need for a false confession.

27:25.567 --> 27:27.700
Eight.

27:27.700 --> 27:31.033
Sir, please don't.

27:31.033 --> 27:34.200
- Nine.
- Sir!

27:34.200 --> 27:37.000
Sir!

27:37.000 --> 27:38.733
Ten.

27:41.567 --> 27:43.333
I...

27:43.333 --> 27:46.967
I killed her, sir.

27:46.967 --> 27:52.933
I killed her, sir.

27:52.933 --> 27:57.000
I'm sorry. I killed her.

27:57.000 --> 28:01.700
I killed her, sir...

28:01.700 --> 28:03.867
[Kangseng Police Station]

28:03.867 --> 28:06.267
Have him write the statement carefully.

28:06.267 --> 28:08.267
So he won't make mistakes
during the crime scene reenactment.

28:08.267 --> 28:11.000
Sure, don't worry.

28:11.000 --> 28:12.700
Sir!

28:12.700 --> 28:14.867
Sir!

28:14.867 --> 28:16.600
- I need to talk to you!
- Hey.

28:16.600 --> 28:17.633
Let's talk, okay?

28:17.633 --> 28:18.767
What on earth are you doing?

28:18.767 --> 28:20.500
What do you mean?

28:20.500 --> 28:22.300
What's going on?

28:22.300 --> 28:23.533
Is he talking to me?

28:23.533 --> 28:26.633
Of course not.
You don't need to worry about it.

28:26.633 --> 28:28.832
He was recently kicked out of Seoul.

28:28.832 --> 28:31.800
Apparently he had trouble there too.

28:32.600 --> 28:33.667
Take care on your way home.

28:33.667 --> 28:35.333
Oh, sir.

28:35.333 --> 28:38.033
- Hello.
- Yes, good work.

28:38.033 --> 28:39.267
Please get home safely.

28:39.267 --> 28:41.967
What's wrong with you, you lunatic?

28:41.967 --> 28:44.100
Didn't you say
the prosecutor got the confession himself?

28:44.100 --> 28:45.467
- Hey.
- So I was going to settle things

28:45.467 --> 28:47.200
- with him!
- Hey, hey!

28:47.200 --> 28:49.280
Kang Tae Joo!

28:49.280 --> 28:52.900
- Let's talk in private, okay?
- Kang Tae Joo?

28:56.567 --> 29:00.333
It is you, Kang Tae Joo!

29:03.767 --> 29:06.867
Wow, Tae Joo, you've really changed.

29:06.867 --> 29:09.200
Hey, Tae Joo!

29:09.200 --> 29:11.833
It's been such a long time.

29:15.000 --> 29:18.600
Wow, didn't expect to see you here!

29:19.633 --> 29:22.333
Hey, good to see you.

29:23.833 --> 29:26.400
So you became a cop?

29:44.533 --> 29:48.633
Tae Joo.

29:51.267 --> 29:54.167
Dead or alive?

29:54.167 --> 29:55.467
[Kang Tae Joo]

29:55.467 --> 29:58.467
[Cha Si Young]

30:40.767 --> 30:43.136
Seems you're in a good mood.

30:43.136 --> 30:47.300
I caught a murderer today.

30:47.300 --> 30:51.600
Such a tough case. Wasn't it hard?

30:51.600 --> 30:56.433
Well, I chose this job out of sense of duty.

30:59.600 --> 31:02.300
My father used to say

31:02.300 --> 31:06.300
that you are someone with great capacity.

31:07.767 --> 31:12.200
It's truly an honor that
the Chairman sees me that way.

31:12.200 --> 31:14.267
I'm really in a good mood today.

31:14.267 --> 31:17.667
Meeting someone as beautiful as you,
Hee Jin, makes it even better.

31:18.400 --> 31:20.100
Oh my.

31:23.633 --> 31:27.867
Actually, I also ran into
an old friend today.

31:28.567 --> 31:31.067
Someone I was very close with.

31:32.400 --> 31:34.100
Mr. Heo.

31:35.033 --> 31:37.056
Kang Tae Joo and Cha Si Young

31:37.056 --> 31:38.874
were classmates.

31:39.533 --> 31:40.733
What are you talking about?

31:40.733 --> 31:43.433
Are Prosecutor Cha Si Young
and Kang Tae Joo classmates?

31:45.233 --> 31:46.367
- Really?
- Yes.

31:46.367 --> 31:47.700
We were surprised too.

31:47.700 --> 31:49.233
They seemed pretty close.

31:49.233 --> 31:52.700
Really? What a small world!

31:52.700 --> 31:54.633
So

31:54.633 --> 31:57.233
did Detective Kang say anything about it?

31:57.233 --> 31:59.300
Right, what is that supposed to mean?

31:59.300 --> 32:02.233
Park Dae Ho, do you know anything?

32:02.233 --> 32:04.133
Well...

32:04.133 --> 32:06.367
It's nothing.

32:06.367 --> 32:08.400
I think I misunderstood earlier.

32:08.400 --> 32:09.733
Don't mind what I said.

32:09.733 --> 32:11.467
See?

32:11.467 --> 32:13.900
We've got the suspect's confession,

32:13.900 --> 32:15.000
and Detective Kang is back.

32:15.000 --> 32:17.367
How about we grab a drink together?

32:17.367 --> 32:20.767
Mr. Heo, since we're all here, how about...

32:20.767 --> 32:22.067
a drink tonight?

32:22.067 --> 32:24.433
Sounds good! How about gopchang?

32:24.433 --> 32:27.100
I've got something I need to do.

32:27.100 --> 32:29.300
Please go ahead without me.

32:29.300 --> 32:34.100
Come on, we're doing this for you.
How can you bail on us?

32:34.100 --> 32:36.500
Just pretend I'm there.

32:37.667 --> 32:39.600
Forget it, forget it.

32:39.600 --> 32:41.533
Never mind.

32:51.000 --> 32:55.967
For the first time since you passed,
I've dressed you in hemp mourning clothes.

32:55.967 --> 33:01.033
[After Laying You Before the Cornfield]
I gave the neighbors some clothes you made.

33:01.033 --> 33:05.433
I buried you beside the cornfield
and walked back.

33:10.533 --> 33:12.233
Go now.

33:12.233 --> 33:13.833
Right now!

33:13.833 --> 33:15.533
Now.

33:32.533 --> 33:36.033
I'm sorry.

33:36.033 --> 33:37.900
I'm sorry.

33:40.267 --> 33:42.367
I'll pay for this.

33:42.367 --> 33:45.533
It's fine. You're just a student.

33:45.533 --> 33:47.967
I'm not some irresponsible kid.

33:47.967 --> 33:49.667
Please let me pay, okay?

33:49.667 --> 33:50.867
That's not your money.

33:50.867 --> 33:52.954
It's your parents'.

33:53.733 --> 33:55.933
You can have this,

33:55.933 --> 33:58.767
so just come to our bookstore
when you buy reference books later.

34:00.933 --> 34:04.500
It's Yu Jeong Rin.

34:09.833 --> 34:13.500
I just wanted to
order the reference books in advance.

34:13.500 --> 34:15.200
Yu Jeong Rin?

34:16.233 --> 34:17.967
I'll write it down.

34:46.833 --> 34:52.500
October 8, 1986, Choi Min Ja, 30 years old.

34:53.200 --> 34:56.233
Found with her hands bound
with a wrapping cloth.

34:56.233 --> 34:57.867
Strangled.

34:57.867 --> 35:01.100
There are signs of manual
strangulation on the neck.

35:02.467 --> 35:07.967
June 11, 1987, Hwang Kang Ae, 21 years old.

35:07.967 --> 35:12.133
Died by strangulation with a scarf.

35:12.133 --> 35:15.233
April 29, 1988.

35:15.967 --> 35:18.633
Im Bok Hee, 29 years old.

35:19.400 --> 35:22.200
Murdered by strangulation with stockings.

35:25.100 --> 35:30.467
If confirmed as serial murders,
the cases will be consolidated.

35:30.467 --> 35:35.567
Choi Min Ja and Hwang Kang Ae cases
were handled by Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon.

35:35.567 --> 35:39.100
Im Bok Hee was assigned to Cha Si Young.

35:40.000 --> 35:42.048
So it'll go

35:42.048 --> 35:44.100
to one of those two.

36:02.533 --> 36:03.733
You're still here?

36:03.733 --> 36:04.733
What are you doing here?

36:04.733 --> 36:06.433
- You didn't even call.
- What is this?

36:06.433 --> 36:07.633
- What is it?
- Should've let me know.

36:07.633 --> 36:10.767
- Hey, hold on.
- Stop.

36:10.767 --> 36:12.067
- What's wrong?
- Hold on.

36:12.067 --> 36:13.433
- Let me see.
- Hey.

36:13.433 --> 36:14.733
Let's go out. Let's go.

36:14.733 --> 36:16.433
- Hold on.
- Alright, let's go.

36:16.433 --> 36:17.600
- Seriously.
- Let's go grab a bite.

36:17.600 --> 36:19.267
Alright, alright.

36:19.267 --> 36:22.600
Isn't the guy in the bookstore really sweet?

36:22.600 --> 36:24.833
He'll remember my name, right?

36:25.800 --> 36:27.567
"It's Yu Jeong Rin."

36:27.567 --> 36:29.867
Hey!

36:29.867 --> 36:32.233
That scared me!

36:32.233 --> 36:34.300
What? It's just a scarecrow.

36:34.300 --> 36:36.100
You startled me.

36:41.533 --> 36:42.900
- Min Ji.
- Yes?

36:42.900 --> 36:44.600
Over there...

36:50.600 --> 36:52.467
Do you know Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon?

36:52.467 --> 36:53.733
Hwang Jae Hoon?

36:53.733 --> 36:54.733
Of course.

36:54.733 --> 36:57.667
Until recently, he was the ace
at the Kangseng District Prosecutors' Office.

36:57.667 --> 36:59.433
He'd never failed to solve a case.

36:59.433 --> 37:02.133
Especially violent crimes.

37:02.133 --> 37:04.160
- And then?
- A suspect being questioned

37:04.160 --> 37:05.967
in the Hwang Kang Ae case killed himself.

37:05.967 --> 37:08.367
And he wasn't even the real culprit.

37:09.467 --> 37:11.667
So who's the ace now?

37:11.667 --> 37:13.467
Prosecutor Cha Si Young.

37:17.633 --> 37:18.933
Why do you ask?

37:18.933 --> 37:21.567
Trying to get close to prosecutors?

37:25.433 --> 37:27.133
You know,

37:28.067 --> 37:31.418
I'm about to lay out a really great spread.

37:32.200 --> 37:34.567
But I don't like the guy holding the spoon.

37:34.567 --> 37:36.167
It takes all the fun out of it.

37:36.167 --> 37:39.167
Then give it to someone else.

37:51.000 --> 37:53.133
What's with that man?

37:53.133 --> 37:54.133
He creeps me out.

37:54.133 --> 37:56.567
I know, he's weird.

37:57.400 --> 37:58.867
Go home. It's late.

38:01.067 --> 38:03.367
What? Did the lights go out?

38:03.367 --> 38:05.133
Seems like it's broken. I'm scared.

38:05.133 --> 38:08.467
I'll make sure
you get home safe, so hurry up.

38:08.467 --> 38:09.467
Really?

38:09.467 --> 38:11.767
Yeah, go on.

38:11.767 --> 38:13.800
I'm going.

38:13.800 --> 38:16.567
Bye, see you tomorrow!

38:43.333 --> 38:45.800
What? Hmph.

38:45.800 --> 38:48.133
You said you'd wait until I got home.

38:48.133 --> 38:50.533
That's low, Yu Jeong Rin.

39:06.767 --> 39:09.533
What should we eat after this?
Gopchang? Rice soup?

39:09.533 --> 39:10.567
Neither sounds good.

39:10.567 --> 39:13.200
Or should we just eat jjajangmyeon?

39:13.200 --> 39:14.400
I'm not feeling jjajangmyeon.

39:14.400 --> 39:15.433
Let's go have sweet and sour pork.

39:15.433 --> 39:17.367
- No, not that either.
- What do you think?

39:18.200 --> 39:20.733
I don't know.

39:20.733 --> 39:21.867
He's coming out.

39:21.867 --> 39:25.133
[New Era, New Police]

39:25.133 --> 39:29.400
Alright, step aside please.

39:31.533 --> 39:33.267
Get in.

39:36.633 --> 39:40.433
[Public Complaints Service Center]

39:42.000 --> 39:45.833
Let's go eat jokbal.

39:50.400 --> 39:51.500
Aren't you going to
the crime scene reenactment?

39:51.500 --> 39:53.567
I've got somewhere to be.

39:55.133 --> 39:57.067
You stay too, as you have work to do.

39:57.067 --> 39:58.767
Me?

39:59.600 --> 40:02.533
They've just headed to the scene.

40:02.533 --> 40:05.533
Departure was delayed by news reporters.

40:05.533 --> 40:06.867
A lot of reporters showed up?

40:06.867 --> 40:10.067
Yeah, looks like all the local papers
in Kangseng showed up.

40:10.067 --> 40:11.867
Do I look okay today?

40:11.867 --> 40:16.300
You're always at your best, sir.

40:16.300 --> 40:18.533
Officer,

40:18.533 --> 40:20.633
you've got a real eye for detail.

40:23.400 --> 40:26.467
Hey, look who's here.

40:26.467 --> 40:28.233
Came to see me?

40:30.033 --> 40:33.167
We're not exactly happy to see each other.

40:35.400 --> 40:38.433
So, how did you
get Lee Seong Jin's confession?

40:38.433 --> 40:40.533
Come on, that hurts.

40:40.533 --> 40:42.400
So you're more curious about him than me?

40:42.400 --> 40:44.133
Did you beat him?

40:44.867 --> 40:46.800
Or threaten him?

40:47.733 --> 40:50.367
You're good at that.

40:50.367 --> 40:54.200
If that's how you did it,
fix it yourself right now.

40:54.200 --> 40:56.433
Don't pin this on an innocent man.

40:58.567 --> 41:01.067
I've got something to say too.

41:03.067 --> 41:05.567
Yeah? What is it?

41:08.800 --> 41:10.833
Just say you're sorry.

41:10.833 --> 41:11.867
It's just that...

41:11.867 --> 41:13.467
Just one word.

41:13.467 --> 41:16.167
I heard you got kicked out of Seoul.

41:17.100 --> 41:19.067
So stop that and come with me.

41:19.067 --> 41:22.067
It's better to catch one murderer
than ten small-time crooks.

41:22.067 --> 41:24.567
Just come and pretend
to go through the reenactment.

41:24.567 --> 41:27.300
I'll put your name on the report.

41:27.300 --> 41:28.512
Well,

41:29.152 --> 41:32.667
I don't stick my nose
into other people's business.

41:32.667 --> 41:36.200
Especially when there's nothing
worth getting involved in.

41:47.933 --> 41:49.600
What are you even talking about?

41:49.600 --> 41:52.600
I'm telling you Lee Seong Jin
is not the real killer.

41:52.600 --> 41:54.500
Why are you telling me this?

41:54.500 --> 41:57.300
Lee Seong Jin isn't
even a suspect in my case...

41:57.300 --> 41:59.833
It's related to your case too, sir.

41:59.833 --> 42:01.900
Choi Min Ja, Hwang Kang Ae,

42:01.900 --> 42:06.333
and Im Bok Hee were
all killed by the same person.

42:06.333 --> 42:08.100
Do you have any evidence?

42:08.100 --> 42:10.200
No, not yet.

42:13.767 --> 42:15.967
What exactly do you want from me?

42:15.967 --> 42:18.767
The crimes all target women
returning home after sunset,

42:18.767 --> 42:21.067
sexual assault,
binding with victims' clothing,

42:21.067 --> 42:23.267
and then strangulation!

42:23.267 --> 42:28.000
What are the chances there are three killers
with the same method in Kangseng?

42:31.400 --> 42:35.833
Let's say, as you claim,
all of this is committed by a serial killer.

42:35.833 --> 42:36.864
Then,

42:36.864 --> 42:39.733
couldn't Lee Seong Jin still be the killer?

42:39.733 --> 42:41.000
Sir.

42:41.000 --> 42:45.760
Lee Seong Jin was in detention
at the time Hwang Kang Ae was killed.

42:48.000 --> 42:50.600
We'll find evidence soon.

42:50.600 --> 42:53.700
The more they kill,
the more addicted they become.

42:53.700 --> 42:55.900
This punk is going to kill again soon.

42:55.900 --> 42:57.633
Possibly...

43:01.467 --> 43:03.833
Yes, Prosecutor Hwang Jae Hoon's office.

43:05.600 --> 43:06.967
As early as today.

43:06.967 --> 43:09.600
Pardon? Who?

43:10.467 --> 43:13.800
Someone is looking for you,
Detective Kang Tae Joo.

43:16.933 --> 43:18.167
Sir!

43:18.167 --> 43:20.133
A body has been found.

43:20.133 --> 43:22.567
It's a murder case.

43:22.567 --> 43:24.267
Okay, I'll be right there.

43:29.133 --> 43:30.867
Evidence has appeared.

43:33.376 --> 43:35.200
Hold it!

43:36.160 --> 43:38.080
I said hold it.

43:39.488 --> 43:42.848
You touched her? You put your hands
all over the person like that?

43:42.848 --> 43:45.333
That's all you've got?

43:47.133 --> 43:51.167
I don't stick my nose
into other people's business.

43:51.167 --> 43:54.867
Especially when there's nothing
worth getting involved in.

43:54.867 --> 43:57.367
"Nothing worth getting involved in?"

44:10.746 --> 44:12.544
[Police]

44:12.544 --> 44:13.600
Jeez.

44:13.600 --> 44:15.333
What is it?

44:16.067 --> 44:17.800
- Hey! Stop!
- Stop him.

44:17.800 --> 44:20.000
Stop, stop, freeze!

44:20.000 --> 44:23.067
Freeze! Stop it...

44:23.067 --> 44:25.000
What are you doing right now?

44:25.000 --> 44:27.033
The reporters are all here!

44:27.933 --> 44:30.000
Well, another body was found.

44:30.000 --> 44:31.424
What does that have to do with this?

44:31.424 --> 44:33.867
- Another body?
- Another one's been found?

44:33.867 --> 44:35.600
- Don't tell me...
- Yes.

44:36.667 --> 44:38.133
Is it true another body has been found?

44:38.133 --> 44:40.933
What about the reenactment?

44:40.933 --> 44:44.133
Sir, is there really another body?

44:44.133 --> 44:46.833
Sir!

44:58.733 --> 45:00.133
Aren't you going to secure the scene?

45:00.133 --> 45:01.433
Secure the scene. Now.

45:01.433 --> 45:03.300
- Step out.
- Wait, but...

45:46.267 --> 45:48.467
[Yu Jeong Rin]
You were right, sir.

45:48.467 --> 45:50.300
It's the same guy.

45:55.467 --> 45:58.967
[You, the Hollyhock]

46:13.867 --> 46:18.333
So the same killer murdered
Yu Jeong Rin and Im Bok Hee?

46:18.333 --> 46:22.667
Yes, the method matches Im Bok Hee's case.

46:22.667 --> 46:26.100
We arrested a guy who wasn't the real killer
and even did a reenactment.

46:26.100 --> 46:28.200
Jeez, if it had gone to trial...

46:28.200 --> 46:30.033
Oh my.

46:30.033 --> 46:31.667
I'm ashamed.

46:31.667 --> 46:34.600
So what are you going to do now?

46:35.232 --> 46:37.920
Since it's definitely the same killer,

46:37.920 --> 46:40.400
we'll indict it together
with Yu Jeong Rin's case...

46:41.533 --> 46:43.300
Come in.

46:47.933 --> 46:50.133
Come sit.

46:54.233 --> 46:58.167
Mr. Hwang thinks differently from you.

46:59.033 --> 47:03.433
It's not two serial murder victims, but four.

47:03.433 --> 47:06.700
The first victim was Choi Min Ja.

47:10.367 --> 47:13.267
Don't you think that's a bit of a stretch?

47:13.267 --> 47:17.200
Choi Min Ja and Hwang Kang Ae
were killed in completely different ways.

47:17.200 --> 47:18.533
It can't be the same killer.

47:18.533 --> 47:19.967
What's different?

47:19.967 --> 47:22.300
Weekdays, after sunset,

47:22.300 --> 47:24.200
crimes targeting women returning home.

47:24.200 --> 47:26.667
And strangulation.

47:26.667 --> 47:31.367
But Im Bok Hee was strangled with stockings.

47:31.367 --> 47:34.433
The killer develops preferences over time.

47:34.433 --> 47:37.300
He used to use
any of the victim's belongings,

47:37.300 --> 47:39.433
but has now become fixated on stockings.

47:39.433 --> 47:41.967
He found that, due to the elasticity,

47:41.967 --> 47:44.900
stockings lead to a slower death
than other materials.

47:45.933 --> 47:48.567
So the goal is a slow death?

47:48.567 --> 47:50.033
Not the texture of it?

47:50.033 --> 47:51.488
That way,

47:52.096 --> 47:54.600
he can prolong the pleasure.

47:54.600 --> 47:56.467
The pleasure of killing.

47:58.400 --> 48:02.600
The next crimes will surely involve
strangulation with stockings.

48:02.600 --> 48:04.433
I'm certain of it.

48:08.967 --> 48:13.367
In any case, you still don't have
direct evidence, do you?

48:13.367 --> 48:15.733
I'll continue my investigation my own way.

48:15.733 --> 48:18.000
Mr. Cha, have you forgotten already?

48:18.000 --> 48:20.400
That you almost wronged an innocent person?

48:23.767 --> 48:25.500
Give me one more chance.

48:25.500 --> 48:28.433
I'm confident this time.

48:38.767 --> 48:40.467
This case...

48:42.464 --> 48:45.800
Excuse me for a second.

49:21.733 --> 49:23.900
Tae Joo

49:25.667 --> 49:28.033
is still so adorable.

49:31.833 --> 49:33.667
What should I do about you?

49:51.100 --> 49:53.667
[You, the Hollyhock]

49:53.667 --> 49:55.367
This book

49:56.433 --> 49:58.900
was found next to Jeong Rin.

49:59.900 --> 50:02.833
The guy from the bookstore gave it to her.

50:03.833 --> 50:05.867
That mark...

50:06.767 --> 50:09.933
That was because of Jeong Rin.

50:16.367 --> 50:18.600
Which bookstore?

50:18.600 --> 50:20.967
Kangseng Bookstore.

50:22.133 --> 50:24.800
That handsome guy there.

50:26.567 --> 50:30.000
Were you on your way home
after stopping by there?

50:32.367 --> 50:34.067
Yes.

50:40.267 --> 50:43.567
Anyone suspicious on the way?

50:53.700 --> 50:55.433
Wait...

50:56.767 --> 50:59.467
I think I know

50:59.467 --> 51:02.167
who killed Jeong Rin.

51:03.867 --> 51:06.067
Who is it?

51:08.667 --> 51:12.033
Min Ji, over there...

51:12.033 --> 51:14.367
Stop right there! I'll catch you!

51:18.900 --> 51:20.600
Shh.

51:23.680 --> 51:25.536
What's going on?

51:37.433 --> 51:40.833
Did you see a woman come this way?

51:41.600 --> 51:43.520
I think she went this way.

51:43.520 --> 51:45.280
Darn it!

51:48.233 --> 51:52.033
Hey, what if you get caught lying?

51:52.033 --> 51:53.376
It's okay.

51:53.376 --> 51:55.100
Let's hurry.

52:01.533 --> 52:08.000
[Specialized Hand Washing for All Shoes]

52:08.633 --> 52:09.633
Hello.

52:09.633 --> 52:11.633
Ms. Kim, you're here.

52:15.100 --> 52:16.633
Nothing special.

52:16.633 --> 52:18.533
No criminal record, either.

52:19.367 --> 52:20.767
One thing suspicious though,

52:20.767 --> 52:24.567
he's been closing the laundry shop
early for months now.

52:26.533 --> 52:29.000
He must be very busy.

52:29.000 --> 52:31.333
Hope today's no different.

52:35.867 --> 52:40.100
[Eun Ho Automatic Laundry]

52:40.100 --> 52:42.100
Duck.

53:12.433 --> 53:14.733
- Shall we go?
- Let's go.

53:37.433 --> 53:39.100
You won't learn until you get hit.

53:39.100 --> 53:40.600
Stop it, don't!

53:40.600 --> 53:41.700
You punk!

53:41.700 --> 53:43.833
Police, are you okay?

53:43.833 --> 53:45.300
Stay still, you punk!

53:45.300 --> 53:46.500
Kim Han Seop!

53:46.500 --> 53:47.600
Stay still, you punk!

53:47.600 --> 53:49.800
- Let go of me!
- Stay still.

53:49.800 --> 53:51.667
Stay still, Kim Han Seop, you'll get hurt.

53:51.667 --> 53:52.667
Who are you?

53:52.667 --> 53:55.433
- I said let go!
- Stay still.

53:56.633 --> 53:59.800
That woman is my wife.

53:59.800 --> 54:02.767
Is it a crime to bring back my runaway wife?

54:09.267 --> 54:11.133
You remember these students?

54:11.133 --> 54:13.867
Three days ago, Dugang-ri underpass.

54:13.867 --> 54:15.600
So?

54:16.533 --> 54:20.900
This one was murdered
right after they ran into you.

54:20.900 --> 54:22.633
What?

54:23.800 --> 54:26.267
It wasn't me! Why would I?

54:26.267 --> 54:29.467
At first, I thought it was a coincidence too.

54:29.467 --> 54:34.167
Until I saw you were about
to stab people with scissors.

54:34.167 --> 54:36.900
I was just trying to scare her.

54:36.900 --> 54:40.333
If I meant to kill her,
I would've brought a knife.

54:40.333 --> 54:41.333
A knife?

54:41.333 --> 54:42.463
I mean,

54:42.463 --> 54:45.867
a knife would be easier to use.

54:47.866 --> 54:49.088
Jeez.

54:55.633 --> 54:57.600
This guy isn't the killer.

54:58.533 --> 55:00.267
Here.

55:00.267 --> 55:02.767
Go ahead.

55:02.767 --> 55:04.600
Thank you.

55:04.600 --> 55:07.100
I ran away from him.

55:07.100 --> 55:10.067
He used to beat me almost every day.

55:10.067 --> 55:14.333
After that, he seemed to be
looking for me every night.

55:16.600 --> 55:20.100
On the 19th around 8 PM,

55:20.100 --> 55:22.967
you ran into these students, right?

55:25.433 --> 55:27.133
Yes.

55:28.667 --> 55:32.900
How long were you
hiding from Kim Han Seop then?

55:32.900 --> 55:36.933
About an hour, I think.

55:36.933 --> 55:40.500
I was there for quite a while,
worried he might come back.

55:41.367 --> 55:45.667
Did Kim Han Seop come back that way again?

55:45.667 --> 55:47.367
No.

55:48.300 --> 55:51.200
Then, anyone who passed by on that road?

55:52.633 --> 55:56.367
No people, though.

55:56.367 --> 55:58.600
"No people?"

55:58.600 --> 56:01.900
Did you notice anything suspicious?

56:01.900 --> 56:05.767
Anything you can remember.

56:05.767 --> 56:07.360
Well,

56:07.360 --> 56:10.067
I'm not entirely sure, but...

56:11.400 --> 56:13.333
Shh.

56:13.333 --> 56:16.533
I'm certain I saw a scarecrow.

56:27.700 --> 56:30.533
But later, it was gone.

56:33.600 --> 56:35.904
A scarecrow...

56:35.904 --> 56:39.100
There was a scarecrow, and...

56:40.767 --> 56:43.777
And I think I heard

56:43.777 --> 56:46.033
stray dogs too.

56:47.267 --> 56:49.200
Where was that?

56:59.367 --> 57:01.067
Hey!

57:03.300 --> 57:05.333
What? It's just a scarecrow.

57:05.333 --> 57:07.067
You startled me.

57:13.500 --> 57:15.233
Min Ji.

58:45.333 --> 58:47.833
Did you see a woman come this way?

58:47.833 --> 58:49.967
I think she went this way.

58:50.633 --> 58:52.367
That day,

58:54.067 --> 58:56.967
the reason the stray dogs
were wary of the scarecrow,

58:58.333 --> 59:02.933
and the reason the victims

59:02.933 --> 59:05.167
weren't wary of him.

59:30.767 --> 59:33.233
Look at this punk.

59:33.233 --> 59:36.100
This guy's completely out of his mind.

59:37.500 --> 59:40.000
You've walked right into my hands now.

01:00:17.100 --> 01:00:19.200
You better hide well.

01:00:19.933 --> 01:00:22.533
And watch your back.

01:00:23.867 --> 01:00:25.767
I'm going to catch you.

01:00:45.433 --> 01:00:47.167
Who's there?

01:00:58.167 --> 01:00:59.900
Who is it?

01:01:05.667 --> 01:01:07.400
Tae Joo?

01:01:09.800 --> 01:01:11.700
It is you, Tae Joo.

01:01:14.433 --> 01:01:15.872
Well,

01:01:15.872 --> 01:01:17.100
why are you here?

01:01:17.100 --> 01:01:19.400
I went to check the Yu Jeong Rin case.

01:01:19.400 --> 01:01:22.267
I thought it might be you.

01:01:22.267 --> 01:01:24.233
Put that thing away.

01:01:24.233 --> 01:01:25.767
Why are you acting so scary?

01:01:25.767 --> 01:01:27.933
So why are you here?

01:01:27.933 --> 01:01:31.100
This isn't even your case anymore.

01:01:31.100 --> 01:01:32.608
Exactly.

01:01:32.608 --> 01:01:34.900
It's not my case anymore.

01:01:34.900 --> 01:01:37.467
I heard you took over this case?

01:01:37.467 --> 01:01:41.400
If you wanted it, you could've just told me.

01:01:41.400 --> 01:01:45.433
Then we could've solved it
together as friends. Isn't it great?

01:01:45.433 --> 01:01:48.700
If you dare say 'us' or 'friends'
in front of me again,

01:01:48.700 --> 01:01:50.900
I'll kill you with my own hands!

01:01:50.900 --> 01:01:52.733
Don't mess with me!

01:01:52.733 --> 01:01:55.867
I'm not the old Kang Tae Joo anymore!

01:01:55.867 --> 01:02:00.067
That guy was patient and naive, but I'm not!

01:02:08.267 --> 01:02:10.433
Stay out of my sight as much as possible.

01:02:10.433 --> 01:02:12.500
It won't take long.

01:02:12.500 --> 01:02:15.067
I don't plan on staying here long anyway.

01:02:18.200 --> 01:02:20.067
Kang Tae Joo!

01:02:24.500 --> 01:02:27.100
I'll take this case back.

01:02:29.800 --> 01:02:31.533
And you too.

01:02:32.900 --> 01:02:33.967
What?

01:02:33.967 --> 01:02:35.168
I will

01:02:35.168 --> 01:02:37.700
keep you by my side.

01:02:37.700 --> 01:02:39.433
Like back then.

01:02:42.300 --> 01:02:44.133
You psycho!

01:02:44.767 --> 01:02:48.233
I missed you, Kang Tae Joo.

01:02:56.200 --> 01:02:58.400
- You punk!
- Hey, hey!

01:02:58.400 --> 01:03:00.167
Hold on, hold on.

01:03:04.333 --> 01:03:06.300
- This way.
- Okay.

01:03:10.010 --> 01:03:13.033
[If you have a dream,
you can always start over]

01:03:13.033 --> 01:03:15.840
I've waited for this day

01:03:15.840 --> 01:03:18.400
for a long time.

01:03:19.800 --> 01:03:22.133
For the past 30 years.

01:03:23.433 --> 01:03:25.400
Hold on.

01:03:25.400 --> 01:03:26.967
Yes?

01:03:26.967 --> 01:03:28.967
Do you have water?

01:03:28.967 --> 01:03:31.933
Yes, it's ready. Let's go.

01:03:37.210 --> 01:03:40.474
[Strong rule of law,
humane and effective corrections]

01:03:40.474 --> 01:03:46.106
[It is about striving
to live a righteous life]

01:04:26.733 --> 01:04:28.567
You're late.

01:04:32.400 --> 01:04:34.133
Have you been

01:04:35.333 --> 01:04:37.467
waiting long?

01:04:44.167 --> 01:04:45.967
Yes.

01:04:47.667 --> 01:04:49.800
Finally, we meet.

01:04:51.267 --> 01:04:53.600
The murderer I've been searching for

01:04:55.500 --> 01:04:57.467
all this time.

01:05:30.600 --> 01:05:33.200
Please help me!

01:05:33.200 --> 01:05:35.133
It felt soft... like a woman's hand.

01:05:35.133 --> 01:05:37.500
If you see anything suspicious
like a scarecrow, run away immediately.

01:05:37.500 --> 01:05:39.233
It might be the killer.

01:05:40.567 --> 01:05:42.233
Detective Kang, I'm the prosecutor

01:05:42.233 --> 01:05:44.500
before I'm your friend.

01:05:44.500 --> 01:05:47.600
If it's a weakness, we can find another one.

01:05:49.333 --> 01:05:52.733
Hey, your sister is in the hospital.

01:05:53.833 --> 01:05:58.367
After what happened to his sister,
what kind of brother wouldn't lose it?
